Rules of procedural fairness have been denied to welfare recipients.305
The crackdown on welfare cheats has raised concerns about a lack of notice that criminal proceedings have begun, and a lack of clarity as to when the investigative process ends and the adversarial process begins. Because the line between the welfare system and criminal justice system has blurred, many questions arise about when a criminal investigation has begun, when a criminal interrogation has begun, and perhaps even when charges are being brought.3 °6
